This paper deals with physical layer security in wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. The paper specifically focuses on the analysis of fading channels, which is a common research area in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with security and privacy, which are topics that fall under computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which could fall under scientific computing (cs.SC) or multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.CR, and cs.NI, followed by cs.SI and cs.MM.
